column1: Debug CAN mapping issue
column31:
This ticket has been created to account for the time invested in debugging a suspected NI issue. Despite using the same blue_marlin.dbc file, Zelos and Grafana are reporting different values for the same signals/messages.

For example, when there is no alarm on the system, Zelos is correctly reading 0 for the value of alarms latched. On the other hand, Grafana reports values between 1.41-1.43 when there is no alarm on the system. Also, some signals (particularly Manta signals) are not being reported on Grafana. Grafana obtains this data from the influxdB, which is also used to validate the plugin tests.

As a result, a lot of the scripts have been failing because the values of the signals used to validate the tests are either reporting incorrectly or not reported at all in Grafana. So the logic fails since the values don’t match. I am currently being supported by Raaga and Yung on this. 



*Zelos (Reporting correct value of 0 for alarms latched)*

!image-20240709-213305.png|width=1164,height=236,alt="image-20240709-213305.png"!



*Grafana/influxdB (Reporting incorrect value of 1.44 for alarms latched)*

!image-20240709-213249.png|width=404,height=242,alt="image-20240709-213249.png"!

column1: Blue Marlin FW Release Testing: June 2024
column31:
Conduct the following tests, which will all be automated, unless manual testing is required:

* V-trip closed loop response (Overvoltage)
* V-trip closed loop response (Undervoltage)
* F trip & accuracy (Over frequency)
* F trip & accuracy (Under frequency)
* Enter Service (Case 1 or Case 5)
* Open phase
* Power charge verification
* Power discharge verification
* Inverter metering accuracy
* Thermal management/temperature read test
* Operational Voltage Range Sweep
* Operational Frequency Range Sweep

column174:
26/Jun/24 6:22 AM;60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9;We are blocked by a [bug|https://generacet.atlassian.net/browse/R2IF-322] that won’t allow the inverter enable in auto mode without reporting an undervoltage alarm. As a result, a lot of effort has been focused on troubleshooting the FW builds on this release.

This also impacted validating newly written automated tests, so we reverted to the previously approved RC’s to be able to do this. Meanwhile, more automated tests are being written and validated, and the code library is constantly being improved.

This ticket is now on hold, and separate tickets with re-evaluated story points will be created to write automated test scripts for the following tests:

* Inverter metering accuracy
* Operational Voltage Range Sweep
* Operational Frequency Range Sweep
column175:
08/Jul/24 9:25 AM;60957172a56f2f006f65f1e9;Scripts now ready for:

* Operational Voltage Range Sweep
* Operational Frequency Range Sweep

island_system.go has also been created and added in the voltron directory for tests that will require the system to be in the islanding state. In this script, the system verifies the system is in islanding state by checking the GSL grid state, checking that the grid lines are low (0V), and checking that the inverter ac lines are high (120V).

column1: Blue Marlin FW Release Testing: June 2024
column31:
Execution of the release test set and pre-compliance test set for Blue Marlin System FW received in June 20th, 2024.
The release candidates tested are:
Manta: 0.9.5 - RC2, RC3
BMU: 0.2.1-RC1, RC2, RC3
INV: 1.10.0-RC2, RC-4
This testing is done to close the loop on these release candidates and ensure stable and reliable FW for alpha sites, test systems, and production.
column98: 24-Q2-KR7.2: Validate BM Firmware Release in 48 Hours
column173:
26/Jun/24 7:34 AM;5e6aa6b89abcc30ce60ca4ef;we are currently blocked on release testing with a [Inverter bug|https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgeneracet.atlassian.net%2Fbrowse%2FR2IF-322&data=05%7C02%7CJoe.Wardwell%40generac.com%7C939309b4eb5e4ff2d75708dc95d9051d%7C3a720757c2fd40b096eb840507006544%7C0%7C0%7C638550006545504768%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=dLorGtAFf45KQlFdaYi5zQbFfCoWByfwh7m%2FADOZJB4%3D&reserved=0] that won’t allow our systems to enable without an undervoltage alarm. This has been present on all RCs we have tested. This issue was repeated on both systems in Waukesha, and we are actively debugging the issue with Tony N.'s help. Details and links to the issue are in our [Issue Summary|https://nam02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgeneracet.atlassian.net%2Fwiki%2Fspaces%2FCTET%2Fpages%2F403570689%2FR2%2BFW%2B-%2BJune%2B24%23Issue-Summary&data=05%7C02%7CJoe.Wardwell%40generac.com%7C939309b4eb5e4ff2d75708dc95d9051d%7C3a720757c2fd40b096eb840507006544%7C0%7C0%7C638550006545515929%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=japYCXUhJgtb%2FAOdCidSrYByB8uFT%2FssmiZ7sfK0gw4%3D&reserved=0] as well.

When we got to the end of our debugging sessions today without a resolution, so we rolled back FW on INV and BMU on our Voltron system to run more automated tests and continue to build out/improve/validate them.
Debugging continues the other system we have in Waukesha. When we get a procedure to correct this issue, or a new RC is available we will bring both systems back up to the release and continue testing.
